race.comment: FORT OF DREAMS (4) is knocking on the door of maiden success, placing in his past couple, getting within a length of the winner last start at Seymour over 1300m. He's got a tricky draw to contend with here but should be able to push forward and any natural improvement will see him hard to beat. KADDARI (9) comes back in trip having hit the line well over a mile at Seymour last time out. A repeat of that effort will see her hard to hold out. SHOTARO (6) is a gelding by Admire Mars on debut for the Busuttin & Young stable. He represents strong connections and should be ready to go. OLIVE ROAD (10) ran well on debut at Cranbourne behind a talented winner and can improve off that. COMMANDEUR (3) is going okay and has minor claims again.
